<item>
            <title>[TIKA-564] Support returning original markup in BoilerpipeContentHandler</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-564</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the BoilerpipeContentHandler emits all non-boilerplate text (as defined by Boilerpipe) as a series of &amp;lt;p&amp;gt;xxx&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt; text blocks, without any markup.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But if you need to find URLs in these blocks, or section headers, then the original markup has to be preserved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately Boilerpipe currently assumes that you have the ability to replay the input stream, and parse it a second time to match up text with what&apos;s been extracted (e.g. see HTMLHighlighter), but with Tika that&apos;s not easy to do - the interface is a ContentHandler, so you don&apos;t have the original inputstream to spool out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead I plan to record the minimum SAX events, and replay those.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
